{"key":"post-7180026","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7180026</id>\n<content>Don't forget to rinse and fill the kettle with hot tap water to begin the soak.  The hot water helps to hydrate the grains during the soak, so that they don't burst when you boil.  The hot water also 'pasteurizes' the rye so it doesn't germinate during the soak.  Weak liquid coffee in the soak/boil water helps colonization and performance, but too much coffee slows down performance.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>7179728</prev>\n<first>7179349</first>\n<last>7180026</last>\n<when>1184541328</when>\n<utime>07/16/07 02:15 AM</utime>\n</post>"}